CRL Website

This project is a simple, static website for the Center for Responsible and Responsive Leadership (CRL). The website is designed using HTML and CSS to provide an elegant and user-friendly interface.

Features

Clean and responsive UI

Well-structured HTML and CSS for easy modifications

Information sections highlighting CRL's mission and objectives

Prerequisites

To run this project locally, you need:

A web browser (Google Chrome, Firefox, Edge, etc.)

A code editor (VS Code, Sublime Text, Notepad++, etc.)

Installation & Setup

Follow these steps to set up the project on your local machine:

Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/crl-website.git

Navigate to the project folder

cd crl-website

Open the project in a browser

Option 1: Double-click the index.html file to open it in your default browser.

Option 2: Use a live server extension (such as in VS Code) to run it locally.

Usage

Once the website is opened in a browser, you can navigate through different sections to explore the information about CRL.

